1
00:00:02,160 --> 00:00:03,685
<i>My name is Oliver Queen.</i>

2
00:00:04,040 --> 00:00:05,246
<i>After five years in hell,</i>

3
00:00:05,520 --> 00:00:09,047
<i>I returned home with only one goal,
to save my city.</i>

4
00:00:09,240 --> 00:00:10,730
<i>But my old approach wasn't enough.</i>

5
00:00:11,040 --> 00:00:12,724
<i>I had to become someone else.</i>

6
00:00:12,920 --> 00:00:15,526
<i>I had to become something else.</i>

7
00:00:15,720 --> 00:00:18,291
<i>I had to become the Green Arrow.</i>

8
00:00:18,920 --> 00:00:20,251
<i>Previously on</i> Arrow...

9
00:00:20,440 --> 00:00:22,044
<i>Those little yellow pills you swallowed,</i>

10
00:00:22,240 --> 00:00:24,402
they do a few interesting things,

11
00:00:24,600 --> 00:00:27,206
including making you cooperative.

12
00:00:27,400 --> 00:00:29,448
Thanks to the algae we engineered
from Star City bay,

13
00:00:29,680 --> 00:00:32,251
the air down here
is now perfectly breathable.

14
00:00:32,440 --> 00:00:35,444
Genesis is almost ready.
We're much too close to play games.

15
00:00:35,600 --> 00:00:37,443
- Do you remember what I promised you?
- A new beginning.

16
00:00:37,720 --> 00:00:39,449
And you will have it.

17
00:00:40,120 --> 00:00:42,566
Once we've brought this world to its end.

18
00:00:43,560 --> 00:00:44,891
Andy's working with Darhk
and has been the entire time.

19
00:00:45,080 --> 00:00:46,047
Andy!

20
00:00:46,240 --> 00:00:47,651
Your brother's way beyond reach,
Mr. Diggle.

21
00:00:47,880 --> 00:00:49,723
If I'd listened to you
instead of trusting my brother,

22
00:00:49,920 --> 00:00:51,126
Laurel would be alive right now.

23
00:00:51,400 --> 00:00:53,129
If Darhk wins, Laurel died for nothing.

24
00:00:53,320 --> 00:00:54,765
He feels unstoppable.

25
00:00:54,960 --> 00:00:56,724
- Because of his magic.
- It's too strong.

26
00:00:56,920 --> 00:00:58,490
You always find a way,

27
00:00:58,880 --> 00:01:01,121
<i>and you have to find a way now.</i>

28
00:01:03,640 --> 00:01:05,802
Now is not the time for panic.

29
00:01:06,080 --> 00:01:07,969
We let him rot in prison.

30
00:01:08,160 --> 00:01:12,131
Clearly, you overestimate
Damien Darhk's capacity for forgiveness,

31
00:01:12,320 --> 00:01:13,765
which is to say that he has any.

32
00:01:13,960 --> 00:01:15,644
Should Damien prove to be unreasonable,

33
00:01:15,840 --> 00:01:18,286
I have implemented contingencies.

34
00:01:19,400 --> 00:01:21,004
My buddies.

35
00:01:21,280 --> 00:01:22,930
Long time, no see.

36
00:01:23,120 --> 00:01:25,088
I brought my posse. Hope you don't mind.

37
00:01:25,520 --> 00:01:26,851
What happened to Ian and Judy?

38
00:01:27,080 --> 00:01:29,526
They come down with that nasty, little flu
that's been going around?

39
00:01:29,680 --> 00:01:32,160
Some were wary of this meeting
given that...

40
00:01:32,440 --> 00:01:34,363
You all abandoned me to my imprisonment?

41
00:01:35,000 --> 00:01:36,286
I visited.

42
00:01:36,480 --> 00:01:38,289
Someone should teach
this evil organization

43
00:01:38,480 --> 00:01:40,448
a lesson in helping their fellow man.

44
00:01:40,640 --> 00:01:42,688
I'm sure it's all
just a simple misunderstanding.

45
00:01:42,920 --> 00:01:46,163
After all, why would I rely solely
on the word of Malcolm Merlyn?

46
00:01:46,360 --> 00:01:49,045
- He can be so underhanded.
- Cute.

47
00:01:49,280 --> 00:01:51,123
And our illustrious council
has worked together

48
00:01:51,320 --> 00:01:52,651
for such a very long time.

49
00:01:52,880 --> 00:01:54,370
I'm glad that we still have your trust.

50
00:01:54,520 --> 00:01:59,048
Of course. I had a lot of time
to reflect while I was in prison,

51
00:01:59,720 --> 00:02:01,802
mostly about religion and bundt cake.

52
00:02:02,000 --> 00:02:04,287
But after much thought, I realized that...

53
00:02:04,520 --> 00:02:06,204
Oh! Almost forgot.

54
00:02:06,480 --> 00:02:09,848
Did my little incarceration
delay Genesis at all?

55
00:02:10,040 --> 00:02:11,371
Of course not.

56
00:02:11,560 --> 00:02:14,530
Genesis is much bigger
than just one person.

57
00:02:19,120 --> 00:02:20,849
Gold star for you.

58
00:02:21,800 --> 00:02:23,404
Where was I? Oh, that's right.

59
00:02:23,560 --> 00:02:25,369
My jailhouse epiphany.

60
00:02:25,560 --> 00:02:27,688
If I could escape prison
without your help,

61
00:02:27,880 --> 00:02:29,530
what do I need any of you for?

62
00:02:33,080 --> 00:02:37,005
Milo, you really have not been
paying attention, have you?

63
00:02:42,240 --> 00:02:44,607
Anyone else care to do something stupid?

64
00:02:45,080 --> 00:02:46,411
No takers?

65
00:02:46,920 --> 00:02:48,081
Pity.

66
00:02:48,920 --> 00:02:52,242
Ladies and gentlemen
and recently deceased,

67
00:02:52,920 --> 00:02:56,925
it is time to begin
the final phase of Genesis.

68
00:03:06,280 --> 00:03:07,247
Milo Armitage.

69
00:03:07,440 --> 00:03:10,410
SCPD found him
in an alley outside Ellendale,

70
00:03:10,600 --> 00:03:12,090
and across town,

71
00:03:13,240 --> 00:03:14,207
Phaedra Nixon.

72
00:03:14,400 --> 00:03:16,562
- Okay. So what am I missing?
- They were both HIVE.

73
00:03:16,800 --> 00:03:17,961
You probably don't recognize
Phaedra and Milo

74
00:03:18,200 --> 00:03:20,931
now that they're dead, or maybe you were
too busy running for your life, but...

75
00:03:21,120 --> 00:03:22,406
They were with Darhk
when he held us hostage.

76
00:03:22,600 --> 00:03:23,726
And now they're dead.

77
00:03:23,920 --> 00:03:26,605
What, so you think
crazy-pants Lonnie Machin's back in town?

78
00:03:26,800 --> 00:03:28,609
No. His grudge is against Darhk, not HIVE.

79
00:03:28,800 --> 00:03:29,801
You think Darhk is cleaning house?

80
00:03:30,040 --> 00:03:32,042
Well, HIVE didn't lift a finger
to break him out of Iron Heights.

81
00:03:32,240 --> 00:03:33,207
That was all Andy and Merlyn.

82
00:03:33,440 --> 00:03:36,125
Okay, well, if Darhk is settling scores,
then now might be the time to hit him.

83
00:03:36,400 --> 00:03:39,927
We have seen how powerful he is.
I can't risk losing anyone else.

84
00:03:40,120 --> 00:03:41,087
We can't just sit on our hands, Oliver.

85
00:03:41,320 --> 00:03:43,926
We're not just sitting on our hands,
but before we do anything,

86
00:03:44,160 --> 00:03:45,924
we need to know
that we can counteract his magic.

87
00:03:46,160 --> 00:03:47,969
Well, is that even possible?

88
00:03:48,320 --> 00:03:49,401
I think it might be.

89
00:03:50,160 --> 00:03:51,650
I was finally able to
get in touch with Constantine

90
00:03:51,880 --> 00:03:52,927
and he put me onto someone

91
00:03:53,120 --> 00:03:56,841
who he thinks may be able to teach me
how to defend against Darhk's magic.

92
00:03:57,000 --> 00:04:00,129
Okay. Well, I'm not just saying this
because I love Harry Potter,

93
00:04:00,320 --> 00:04:02,846
but why are we not all
taking those lessons?

94
00:04:03,000 --> 00:04:06,607
Well, it is easier said than done,
and apparently, quite dangerous.

95
00:04:08,480 --> 00:04:11,245
So, I have to go to Hub City
for a day or two.

96
00:04:11,840 --> 00:04:14,969
Okay. In that case,
can I take the weekend with Alex?

97
00:04:15,160 --> 00:04:17,686
Kind of wants to go away, clear our heads.

98
00:04:17,920 --> 00:04:20,127
That sounds like a good idea.
I think that...

99
00:04:20,360 --> 00:04:21,964
Actually, I think everyone should
take a little time.

100
00:04:22,760 --> 00:04:26,810
Lay low, but stay available, and
we will deal with Darhk when I get back.

101
00:04:28,000 --> 00:04:29,206
Okay.

102
00:04:34,360 --> 00:04:35,361
Let him in.

103
00:04:40,840 --> 00:04:41,841
Mind stepping out?

104
00:04:42,200 --> 00:04:44,362
"HEY. you. How you holding up?"

105
00:04:44,840 --> 00:04:47,889
You've, um, looked better.

106
00:04:48,880 --> 00:04:51,724
Considering I've spent two weeks
in a bomb-proof tungsten-encased bunker,

107
00:04:51,880 --> 00:04:52,881
I think I look pretty good.

108
00:04:54,680 --> 00:04:55,727
You hungry?

109
00:04:56,320 --> 00:04:58,527
Mmm. How long have those been there?

110
00:04:58,720 --> 00:05:00,722
That was lunch.
It might have even been today's.

111
00:05:00,960 --> 00:05:02,405
Yeah, I think I'll pass.

112
00:05:02,720 --> 00:05:05,564
Oliver is leaving tonight
on some Magical Mystery Tour.

113
00:05:05,800 --> 00:05:09,043
He wants me to stay put and do nothing
until he comes back.

114
00:05:09,320 --> 00:05:10,321
Magical Mystery Tour?

115
00:05:10,560 --> 00:05:12,164
Yeah, it's a long story.

116
00:05:12,360 --> 00:05:16,160
But the point of it is that he thinks
it's too dangerous for any of us

117
00:05:16,360 --> 00:05:19,330
to go after Darhk or Andy
until he gets the right magical know-how.

118
00:05:19,720 --> 00:05:21,563
- I can see you're thrilled about that.
- Mmm.

119
00:05:21,840 --> 00:05:23,080
If you think you have it bad,

120
00:05:23,320 --> 00:05:25,891
try remembering you're not the one
being held prisoner in a metal box.

121
00:05:26,080 --> 00:05:27,889
Look, sweetheart.

122
00:05:28,840 --> 00:05:30,205
We've talked about this.

123
00:05:30,400 --> 00:05:33,210
Andy has been inside of A.R.G.U.S.
He's been inside of our home.

124
00:05:34,160 --> 00:05:36,242
It's too dangerous for you
to be either place right now.

125
00:05:38,920 --> 00:05:41,366
I don't want you in either place, either.

126
00:05:44,760 --> 00:05:47,047
Oh, I got you. I got you.

127
00:05:48,840 --> 00:05:51,571
<i>- Let my agents see what they can find.
- Yeah.</i>

128
00:05:51,760 --> 00:05:53,922
<i>And, as much as you don't wanna hear it,</i>

129
00:05:54,600 --> 00:05:56,284
- Oliver has a point.
- Mmm.

130
00:05:56,840 --> 00:05:59,571
HIVE is too dangerous for you
to go off half-cocked, John.

131
00:05:59,920 --> 00:06:01,763
Well, it's always serious
when you call me "John."

132
00:06:02,040 --> 00:06:05,123
Well, John, why don't you
make yourself useful

133
00:06:05,280 --> 00:06:06,805
by grabbing some diapers while you're out.

134
00:06:07,400 --> 00:06:09,528
We're running low,
and I hate asking my people to get them.

135
00:06:09,760 --> 00:06:11,649
- You got it.
- Mmm-hmm.

136
00:06:13,240 --> 00:06:15,288
- Back in an hour?
- Or less.

137
00:06:17,040 --> 00:06:18,804
Good-bye, Daddy. Honey, say bye.

138
00:06:37,520 --> 00:06:40,603
- You've been living down here?
- Seemed to make the most sense.

139
00:06:40,800 --> 00:06:41,881
Where's all your stuff?

140
00:06:42,480 --> 00:06:44,482
It's just in storage.
You know me, I don't need much.

141
00:06:45,000 --> 00:06:46,126
Maybe like a plant?

142
00:06:46,320 --> 00:06:50,166
Like a fern or something.
They thrive in places like this.

143
00:06:50,840 --> 00:06:54,481
How could I forget? Come to see me off?

144
00:06:54,720 --> 00:06:55,846
You were pretty stingy on the details

145
00:06:56,040 --> 00:06:59,010
about this "magic tutor"
Constantine referred you to.

146
00:06:59,200 --> 00:07:00,326
That is, sort of, my MO.

147
00:07:00,520 --> 00:07:02,010
Don't talk to me like I'm other people.

148
00:07:04,400 --> 00:07:05,561
What has you so worried?

149
00:07:05,800 --> 00:07:08,804
Darhk's idol,
the type of magic that he's using,

150
00:07:09,000 --> 00:07:11,241
I've seen it take good people

151
00:07:12,720 --> 00:07:16,645
and turn them dark, soulless,
and almost inhuman.

152
00:07:16,960 --> 00:07:18,246
And you're afraid
that's gonna happen to you?

153
00:07:18,480 --> 00:07:20,164
There's an argument to be made
that I'm already there.

154
00:07:20,360 --> 00:07:22,044
- That's not funny.
- I am not joking.

155
00:07:23,680 --> 00:07:28,891
There is no length that I will not go to,
to avenge Laurel.

156
00:07:30,520 --> 00:07:32,329
To stop Darhk
from hurting anyone ever again.

157
00:07:34,320 --> 00:07:37,164
And I honestly don't know
where that path will lead.

158
00:07:37,360 --> 00:07:38,885
I'm coming with you.

159
00:07:40,040 --> 00:07:41,007
Felicity.

160
00:07:41,200 --> 00:07:42,531
Just because we're not together

161
00:07:42,760 --> 00:07:44,410
doesn't mean you have to do this alone.

162
00:07:44,600 --> 00:07:46,921
And, I've already chartered
the company jet. Mr. Dennis was furious.

163
00:07:47,160 --> 00:07:51,404
And I've booked us a room, rooms.
With points.

164
00:07:51,840 --> 00:07:53,604
Should I even try
and talk you out of this?

165
00:07:53,880 --> 00:07:56,929
No. You've met my mother.
Same DNA.

166
00:08:25,240 --> 00:08:26,241
Did you see anyone else here?

167
00:08:27,240 --> 00:08:30,483
Which way? Get out of here, now.

168
00:08:41,240 --> 00:08:42,730
What the hell?

169
00:08:44,600 --> 00:08:45,965
Sorry, man.

170
00:08:46,120 --> 00:08:48,771
But I'm not playing anymore! Whoo!

171
00:08:49,120 --> 00:08:53,603
You still got those quick reflexes, John.
Too bad they couldn't save your partner.

172
00:08:53,840 --> 00:08:55,285
Don't you dare say anything about her!

173
00:08:55,440 --> 00:08:57,488
Well, you got a gun. Make me!

174
00:09:29,600 --> 00:09:31,523
Hey, honey, it's a little tough for me
to talk right now.

175
00:09:31,800 --> 00:09:34,326
You'll wanna hear this,
satellite track just picked up Andy.

176
00:09:36,440 --> 00:09:39,330
Let me guess, he's somewhere south of Main
between Grammercy and Addison, right?

177
00:09:39,640 --> 00:09:40,641
How do you know that?

178
00:09:40,840 --> 00:09:42,490
Because I'm trading shots with him
right now.

179
00:09:42,680 --> 00:09:45,160
- Johnny.
- Yell at me later. Just send backup.

180
00:09:45,360 --> 00:09:47,169
He's at the Grammercy Power Plant.

181
00:09:47,520 --> 00:09:49,010
<i>How soon can your men get here?</i>

182
00:09:50,000 --> 00:09:51,001
Five minutes, ten tops.

183
00:09:51,160 --> 00:09:52,366
That's too long.

184
00:09:53,000 --> 00:09:54,001
<i>Johnny, you need to wait.</i>

185
00:09:54,160 --> 00:09:56,003
You have no tactical advantage in there.

186
00:09:56,160 --> 00:09:59,403
Well, I can't wait. If I do, he gets away.
I can't let that happen. Not again.

187
00:09:59,640 --> 00:10:00,971
Your judgment is compromised.

188
00:10:01,200 --> 00:10:04,363
Maybe it is.
But it doesn't mean I'm wrong. Get here!

189
00:10:06,520 --> 00:10:09,171
Johnny! Johnny!

190
00:10:13,880 --> 00:10:16,087
So, what exactly are we looking for?

191
00:10:16,320 --> 00:10:17,242
High roller room.

192
00:10:17,480 --> 00:10:20,370
When you said that you had found someone
to teach you magic, I was thinking, like,

193
00:10:20,560 --> 00:10:22,210
a mountain top or a hidden temple,

194
00:10:22,400 --> 00:10:25,324
not Hub City's
premiere underground casino.

195
00:10:26,160 --> 00:10:29,209
Well, with Constantine, I have learned
to expect the unexpected.

196
00:10:31,720 --> 00:10:32,767
I'm betting on Fortuna.

197
00:10:35,560 --> 00:10:39,087
Now, he was a little bit vague
with the specifics. He just said,

198
00:10:39,360 --> 00:10:42,921
"Pitch game, first base, mate,
see if you're worthy."

199
00:10:43,200 --> 00:10:44,201
Wow.

200
00:10:44,720 --> 00:10:46,085
Okay, pitch game, blackjack,

201
00:10:46,360 --> 00:10:48,408
uh, dealer using up to two decks.

202
00:10:48,720 --> 00:10:51,371
"First base,"
first seat on the dealer's left.

203
00:10:51,560 --> 00:10:53,562
I think we're in the right place.

204
00:10:53,720 --> 00:10:56,087
I'm not so sure that finding this guy
depends on gambling.

205
00:10:56,240 --> 00:10:57,890
It's not gambling when I play.

206
00:11:12,280 --> 00:11:13,441
Alex?

207
00:11:31,720 --> 00:11:34,610
Hello? Alex?

208
00:11:43,640 --> 00:11:44,766
Alex?

209
00:11:45,960 --> 00:11:49,965
Hey, morning. And here I thought
you were gonna sleep past breakfast.

210
00:11:51,640 --> 00:11:56,487
I almost did. I'm so foggy.

211
00:11:56,640 --> 00:12:00,611
Yeah, you were exhausted. You passed out
five minutes after we left the city.

212
00:12:00,800 --> 00:12:01,801
Oh.

213
00:12:02,680 --> 00:12:04,330
Guess I was really tired.

214
00:12:04,480 --> 00:12:07,689
See, it just proves how badly
you needed this trip. We both did.

215
00:12:08,640 --> 00:12:10,608
Now, you ready for some
famous eggs Benedict?

216
00:12:11,320 --> 00:12:13,049
You poached eggs?

217
00:12:13,280 --> 00:12:16,648
Hey, I'm not just a cutthroat
political operative. I contain multitudes.

218
00:12:17,000 --> 00:12:20,049
Mmm-hmm.
And you also wear a very mean apron.

219
00:12:20,320 --> 00:12:21,970
Well, you should see
what I have on underneath.

220
00:12:22,160 --> 00:12:23,844
Mmm.

221
00:12:28,440 --> 00:12:29,805
I forgot how good you were at this.

222
00:12:30,000 --> 00:12:31,684
Ah, like riding a bike.

223
00:12:33,000 --> 00:12:34,047
Rough beat.

224
00:12:34,320 --> 00:12:37,369
Indeed. I should probably head home soon
before they take my shoes.

225
00:12:37,520 --> 00:12:40,330
Well, you never know
when your luck's gonna change. Trust me.

226
00:12:42,040 --> 00:12:44,202
<i>That's so kind. Muchas gracias.</i>

227
00:12:44,640 --> 00:12:45,846
<i>De</i> nada.

228
00:12:47,240 --> 00:12:48,241
Oh, boom!

229
00:12:48,680 --> 00:12:52,810
Come to mama. I mean. What?

230
00:12:53,320 --> 00:12:56,005
I'm starting to think
that this guy's gonna be a no-show.

231
00:12:56,200 --> 00:12:57,201
Right.

232
00:12:57,360 --> 00:13:00,045
It's because he's not a guy, amor.

233
00:13:00,520 --> 00:13:02,045
Esrin Fortuna.

234
00:13:03,040 --> 00:13:05,725
Tell John Constantine
he still owes me money.

235
00:13:16,840 --> 00:13:18,842
Stay right where you are,
you son of a bitch!

236
00:13:19,560 --> 00:13:20,925
It's funny.

237
00:13:23,280 --> 00:13:24,725
I was gonna tell you the same thing.

238
00:13:29,200 --> 00:13:30,884
Bravo, John.

239
00:13:31,560 --> 00:13:33,130
You played the script out perfectly.

240
00:13:33,880 --> 00:13:35,211
What the hell are you talking about?

241
00:13:35,400 --> 00:13:37,528
Oh, don't worry about it.
I'll explain everything.

242
00:13:39,080 --> 00:13:40,241
After you wake up.

243
00:13:50,520 --> 00:13:52,204
Sorry, this place isn't as fancy

244
00:13:52,400 --> 00:13:54,402
as the cage you kept me in
for three months.

245
00:13:56,400 --> 00:13:57,606
Where the hell am I?

246
00:13:57,760 --> 00:14:00,650
