00:32:31,480 --> 00:32:33,528
It's a small world, isn't it?

490
00:32:33,720 --> 00:32:36,451
Your brother-in-law
being my loyal servant.

491
00:32:36,680 --> 00:32:40,446
Thanksgiving at your home
is gonna be so interesting this year.

492
00:33:05,560 --> 00:33:09,007
You seem like a likable guy, Oliver.
I bet you've got a lot of friends.

493
00:33:09,240 --> 00:33:11,686
I'm going to enjoy
killing every last one of them.

494
00:33:13,240 --> 00:33:14,924
No. Never again.

495
00:33:37,080 --> 00:33:39,321
I bet you regret not pulling that trigger
the first time around.

496
00:33:42,320 --> 00:33:43,731
What are you gonna do, John?

497
00:33:51,520 --> 00:33:55,206
After Laurel, I left you alone to grieve.
I was being nice.

498
00:33:55,640 --> 00:33:57,802
You have no idea
how much I hate being nice.

499
00:34:23,480 --> 00:34:24,447
It isn't over.

500
00:34:24,640 --> 00:34:26,449
You haven't been paying attention, Andy.

501
00:34:26,640 --> 00:34:30,406
Darhk got out. I got out.
I'll get out again.

502
00:34:31,680 --> 00:34:35,162
That mobile safe-house you've got
looked really homey.

503
00:34:35,560 --> 00:34:37,403
Bet it gets cramped once Sara gets older.

504
00:34:39,120 --> 00:34:40,167
Shut up.

505
00:34:40,360 --> 00:34:41,930
She's gotta go to school eventually.

506
00:34:42,960 --> 00:34:46,203
And Lyla, well, you can't watch her 24/7.

507
00:34:46,400 --> 00:34:49,483
I said, "Shut your mouth," Andy.
Shut your damn mouth!

508
00:34:49,920 --> 00:34:54,448
You're the one who's obviously
not payin' attention. Because this is war.

509
00:34:54,640 --> 00:34:58,406
And women, children,
they're expendable in your war?

510
00:34:58,600 --> 00:35:00,648
Genesis is coming, John.

511
00:35:02,040 --> 00:35:04,611
Lyla and Sara won't be
the only women and children who die.

512
00:35:06,800 --> 00:35:12,807
Tell me, how does it feel knowing that
you had no problem pulling the trigger

513
00:35:13,040 --> 00:35:15,646
to protect a bunch of Afghanis
that you never knew,

514
00:35:16,120 --> 00:35:19,363
<i>but you don't have the guts
to do what's necessary,</i>

515
00:35:19,720 --> 00:35:21,324
to protect your own wife and child?

516
00:35:53,040 --> 00:35:54,405
How's Lyla?

517
00:35:56,080 --> 00:35:57,081
Um...

518
00:35:59,000 --> 00:36:00,047
She's fine.

519
00:36:00,280 --> 00:36:01,281
She's... Uh...

520
00:36:02,200 --> 00:36:04,567
She unconscious, but she's fine.

521
00:36:04,840 --> 00:36:09,448
Felicity's taking her and Sara back.
Darhk is... Darhk's in the wind.

522
00:36:12,880 --> 00:36:14,689
John, what happened?

523
00:36:16,880 --> 00:36:19,451
He was never gonna back off, Oliver.

524
00:36:23,320 --> 00:36:24,685
My family,

525
00:36:26,360 --> 00:36:28,249
they were never gonna be safe.

526
00:36:38,920 --> 00:36:40,410
- Hey.
- Hi.

527
00:36:42,920 --> 00:36:45,048
- Did you get in touch with Thea?
- Not yet.

528
00:36:47,200 --> 00:36:48,247
You Okay?

529
00:36:51,680 --> 00:36:54,001
Earlier, with Darhk, it worked.

530
00:36:54,640 --> 00:36:57,610
He tried to use his magic on me,
and I was able to repel it.

531
00:36:57,800 --> 00:36:58,881
That's incredible.

532
00:37:00,520 --> 00:37:01,885
How'd you do it?

533
00:37:06,640 --> 00:37:08,881
I heard your voice in my head.

534
00:37:10,240 --> 00:37:12,083
You were reminding me
of all the good things

535
00:37:12,280 --> 00:37:13,611
that I have in my life.

536
00:37:15,760 --> 00:37:17,649
I heard Thea, I heard John.

537
00:37:20,400 --> 00:37:21,686
I heard Laurel.

538
00:37:24,560 --> 00:37:27,643
Just telling me to keep fighting,
to never give up.

539
00:37:29,720 --> 00:37:31,688
Just telling me to have hope.

540
00:37:42,840 --> 00:37:43,921
Hey-

541
00:37:45,400 --> 00:37:49,041
- Sara? Where's Sara?
- No, no, no. She's fine. She's fine.

542
00:37:49,280 --> 00:37:51,248
Felicity took her to Donna. She's okay.

543
00:37:57,400 --> 00:37:58,561
But something's wrong.

544
00:38:06,840 --> 00:38:07,841
I, um...

545
00:38:09,720 --> 00:38:11,882
I had to put him down, Lyla.

546
00:38:15,000 --> 00:38:16,126
(And)'-

547
00:38:19,320 --> 00:38:21,641
I had to kill my baby brother.

548
00:38:22,600 --> 00:38:25,080
He wasn't a brother to you, Johnny.

549
00:38:26,760 --> 00:38:28,444
Not in the ways that really matter.

550
00:38:31,000 --> 00:38:32,570
What happened?

551
00:38:39,000 --> 00:38:40,889
He reached for my gun.

552
00:38:44,720 --> 00:38:46,324
I didn't have a choice.

553
00:38:58,200 --> 00:39:00,965
- Oh, no. No, no, no.
- What? What?

554
00:39:04,440 --> 00:39:08,684
It's gone. Darhk took it.

555
00:39:10,200 --> 00:39:11,201
Took what?

556
00:39:14,240 --> 00:39:15,526
Rubicon.

557
00:39:16,840 --> 00:39:18,763
I thought Rubicon was being stored
at A.R.G.U.S.

558
00:39:19,000 --> 00:39:22,129
It was,
until Shadowspire tried to steal it.

559
00:39:22,960 --> 00:39:25,850
After Waller's death, I had it moved
for security reasons.

560
00:39:26,040 --> 00:39:27,041
To where?

561
00:39:29,000 --> 00:39:30,001
It was under your skin?

562
00:39:30,200 --> 00:39:33,329
A subdermal implant. Darhk ripped it out.

563
00:39:33,520 --> 00:39:36,364
Lyla, you need to tell us what Rubicon is.

564
00:39:38,000 --> 00:39:40,128
A ballistic launch override protocol,

565
00:39:40,320 --> 00:39:42,402
designed to prevent any country,
even our own,

566
00:39:42,600 --> 00:39:44,090
from firing a nuclear missile.

567
00:39:44,280 --> 00:39:47,329
Something tells me
Darhk's plans aren't so benign.

568
00:39:51,480 --> 00:39:54,404
<i>With some work
and the right expertise,</i>

569
00:39:54,640 --> 00:39:56,244
<i>Rubicon could be corrupted.</i>

570
00:39:57,080 --> 00:39:59,367
Instead of controlling nukes
to prevent them from being launched...

571
00:39:59,560 --> 00:40:00,527
Oh, my God.

572
00:40:00,720 --> 00:40:02,529
Darhk would control
the world's nuclear stockpile.

573
00:40:02,720 --> 00:40:06,167
To what end? I don't mean to apply logic
to a bad guy's plot here,

574
00:40:06,360 --> 00:40:09,887
but Darhk destroys the world, then what?
He'd be ruler of nothing.

575
00:40:10,080 --> 00:40:14,642
Unless he wants to rebuild.
Andy told me that "Genesis" was coming.

576
00:40:14,840 --> 00:40:16,968
I don't think so. Phil Collins said
they'd never tour again.

577
00:40:17,160 --> 00:40:19,925
The Old Testament. The book of Genesis.

578
00:40:20,640 --> 00:40:22,847
God wanted to give the world a do-over
so he destroyed it.

579
00:40:23,040 --> 00:40:24,485
He destroyed it with a flood.

580
00:40:25,280 --> 00:40:26,930
Rubicon is Darhk's flood.

581
00:40:33,280 --> 00:40:35,681
<i>So, nuclear annihilation
is Darhk's flood,</i>

582
00:40:36,480 --> 00:40:38,642
what's he planning on building as his ark?

583
00:41:47,880 --> 00:41:48,881
English - SDH

